'''''Star Wars Insider'' 37''' is the thirty-seventh issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[April]] [[1998]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"The Editor's Desk" by Jon Bradley Snyder
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Prequel Profile]]: Keith Hamshere" {{C|by [[Pamela Roller]]}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe: Maria de Aragon]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" {{C|by [[Peet Janes]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Something Wicked This Way Comes]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Scott Chernoff talks with the actor who will portray Senator Palpatine in ''Star Wars'': Episode I.</small>
*"[[Peter Cushing: Charming to the Last]]" {{C|by [[Constantine Nasr]]}}
*:<small>A retrospective look at the great British star who played Grand Moff Tarkin&mdash;by Constantine Nasr.</small>
*"[[Return to Hoth (article)|Return to Hoth]]" {{C|by [[Arnd Riede]]}}
*:<small>An intrepid writer from Germany sets foot on the ice-field in Norway where ''The Empire Strikes Back'' was filmed.</small>
*"[[Jack Purvis Remembered]]" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*:<small>Jamie Painter looks into the life of one of the unsung heroes of the ''Star Wars'' trilogy.</small>
*"[[1997 Star Wars Customizable Card Game World Championship|1997 ''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game World Championship]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>Find out who won the ultimate ''Star Wars'' battle in Norfolk, VA.</small>

